    "Higher outdegrees indicate more significant influence and a higher probability of being cited by different categories of literature.",
    "As shown in Figure 3 (b), the literature on genetic algorithms cites a genetic algorithms literature i and a probabilistic methods literature k. However, the literature k can also be referenced in the literature within the field of neural networks.",
    "The correlation between (i → j) and (k → j) is influenced by the out-degree of the citing nodes i and k.",
    "A e,(i→j),(k→j) = exp",
    "where deg + (i) and deg + (k) denote the out-degree of node i and node k. Literature with lesser out-degrees is more likely to be cited by literature from the same category."
